#: ../../software/software-monitor.rst:36
msgid ""
"The *selection state* influences the action taken when updating a "
"package. ``Install`` is used to select a package for installation. If a "
"package is configured to ``Hold`` it will be excluded from further "
"updates. There are two possibilities for uninstalling a package: A "
"package removed with ``DeInstall`` keeps locally created configuration "
"data, whilst a package removed with ``Purge`` is completely deleted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/software-monitor.rst:47
msgid "Installation state"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/software-monitor.rst:44
msgid ""
"The *installation state* describes the status of an installed package in "
"relation to upcoming updates. The normal status is ``Ok``, which leads to"
" a package being updated when a newer version exists. If a package is "
"configured to ``Hold`` it will be excluded from the update."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/software-monitor.rst:53
msgid "Package state"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/software-monitor.rst:50
msgid ""
"The *package state* describes the status of a setup package. The normal "
"status here is ``Installed`` for installed packages and ``ConfigFiles`` "
"for removed packages. All other statuses appear when the package's "
"installation was canceled in different phases."
msgstr ""

