msgid "Differentiation of update variants / UCS versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:6
msgid "Four types of UCS updates are differentiated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:11
msgid "Major releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:9
msgid ""
"*Major releases* appear approximately every three to four years. Major "
"releases can differ significantly from previous major releases in terms "
"of their scope of services, functioning and the software they contain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:21
msgid "Minor releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:14
msgid ""
"During the maintenance period of a major release, *minor releases* are "
"released approximately every 10-12 months. These updates include "
"corrections to recently identified errors and the expansion of the "
"product with additional features. At the same time and as far as this is "
"possible, the minor releases are compatible with the previous versions in"
" terms of their functioning, interfaces and operation. Should a change in"
" behavior prove practical or unavoidable, this will be noted in the "
"release notes when the new version is published."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:25
msgid "Patchlevel releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:24
msgid ""
"*Patchlevel releases* are released approximately every three months and "
"combine all errata updates published until then."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:31
msgid "Errata updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:28
msgid ""
"Univention continuously releases *errata updates*. Errata updates provide"
" fixes for security vulnerabilities, bug fixes, and smaller enhancements "
"to make them available to customer systems quickly. An overview of all "
"errata updates can be found at https://errata.software-univention.de/."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:33
msgid ""
"Every released UCS version has an unambiguous version number; it is "
"composed of a figure (the major version), a full stop, a second figure "
"(the minor version), a hyphen and a third figure (the patch level "
"version). The version UCS 4.2-1 thus refers to the first patch level "
"update for the second minor update for the major release UCS 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:39
msgid ""
"The *pre-update script* :file:`preup.sh` is run before every release "
"update. It checks for example whether any problems exist, in which case "
"the update is canceled in a controlled manner. The *post-update script* "
":file:`postup.sh` is run at the end of the update to perform additional "
"cleanups, if necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:44
msgid ""
"Errata updates always refer to certain minor releases, e.g., for UCS 5.0."
" Errata updates can generally be installed for all patch level versions "
"of a minor release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/ucs-versions.rst:48
msgid ""
"If a new release or errata updates are available, a corresponding "
"notification is given when a user opens a UMC module. The availability of"
" new updates is also notified via email; the corresponding newsletters - "
"separated into release and error updates - can be subscribed on the "
"Univention website. A changelog document is published for every release "
"update listing the updated packages, information on error corrections and"
" new functions and references to the Univention Bugzilla."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:4
msgid "Updates of UCS systems"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:6
msgid ""
"There are two ways to update UCS systems; either on individual systems "
"(via UMC module :guilabel:`Software update` or command line) or via a "
"computer policy for larger groups of UCS systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:13
msgid "Update strategy in environments with more than one UCS system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:15
msgid ""
"In environments with more than one UCS system, the update order of the "
"UCS systems must be borne in mind."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:18
msgid ""
"The authoritative version of the LDAP directory service is maintained on "
"the |UCSPRIMARYDN| and replicated on all the remaining LDAP servers of "
"the UCS domain. As changes to the LDAP schemes (see :ref:`domain-ldap-"
"schema`) can occur during release updates, the |UCSPRIMARYDN| **must "
"always be the first system** to be updated during a release update."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:24
msgid ""
"It is generally advisable to update all UCS systems in one maintenance "
"window whenever possible. If this is not possible, all not-updated UCS "
"systems should only be one release version older compared with the "
"|UCSPRIMARYDN|."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:32
msgid "Updating individual systems via |UCSUMC| module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:34
msgid ""
"The UMC module :guilabel:`Software update` allows the installation of "
"release updates and errata updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../software/updates.rst:37
msgid ""
":numref:`software-umc-update` shows the overview page of the module. The "
"currently installed version is displayed under :guilabel:`Release "
"updates`."
msgstr ""

